---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const title = 'About Me';
const description = 'Learn more about the developer behind The Calm Developer blog.';
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={description} canonicalPath="/about/">
	<div class="site-inner">
		<section class="page-hero">
			<div class="page-hero-copy surface-card">
				<p class="eyebrow">About the author</p>
				<h1 class="page-heading">
					Building calm software starts with understanding what sits underneath the abstractions.
				</h1>
				<p class="page-subtitle">
					I&apos;m Harrison, a software engineer focused on reliable systems, steady
					frontend craftsmanship, and learning the machine-level details that make
					software hold up over time.
				</p>
			</div>
			<aside class="surface-card utility-card">
				<p class="utility-label">Connect</p>
				<p class="utility-copy">
					I am always open to discussing software, systems, and interesting
					engineering problems.
				</p>
				<div class="link-stack">
					<a href="https://github.com/hstephan23">GitHub</a>
					<a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/harrison-stephan-software-engineer/">LinkedIn</a>
					<a href="mailto:thecalmdeveloper@gmail.com">Email</a>
				</div>
			</aside>
		</section>

		<div class="info-grid">
			<section class="surface-card info-card">
				<p class="eyebrow">Background</p>
				<h2 class="section-title">What I am focused on</h2>
				<p>
					I work primarily with C today, but I started my career in modern web
					technologies as a TypeScript and React frontend specialist.
				</p>
				<p>
					Lately I have been especially interested in memory, performance, and the
					low-level reasons software behaves the way it does.
				</p>
			</section>
			<section class="surface-card info-card">
				<p class="eyebrow">Expertise</p>
				<h2 class="section-title">Areas of practice</h2>
				<ul class="clean-list">
					<li>
						<strong>Systems and low-level programming:</strong> C, memory management,
						and performance thinking.
					</li>
					<li>
						<strong>Frontend engineering:</strong> React, TypeScript, and maintainable
						UI architecture.
					</li>
					<li>
						<strong>Software design:</strong> Building systems that stay readable and
						reliable as they grow.
					</li>
				</ul>
			</section>
			<section class="surface-card info-card">
				<p class="eyebrow">Philosophy</p>
				<h2 class="section-title">Why this blog exists</h2>
				<p>
					The idea behind The Calm Developer is simple: write code that is easy to
					read, simple to maintain, and grounded in real engineering tradeoffs.
				</p>
				<p>
					This site is where I share what I am learning as I dig deeper into the
					machine, the principles underneath the abstractions, and the craft of
					software that lasts.
				</p>
			</section>
		</div>
	</div>
</BaseLayout>
